(428, 'Notes: Surfacing Selkea , this is an ex RBI H bank compliance focused team (starting with an AMA compliance bot trained on RBI circulars).Founders claim to have been part of the creation of the mule account identifier and ULI at RBIH. Raising a $1M round , claim to have commits from Rajesh Bansal and a few other RBI folks as angels who will also come on board as advisors. **Founders** [**Abhishek Mishra**](https://www.linkedin.com/in/abhishekmishra96/) - Senior Assc (CEOs office RBI H) , MT - RBL Bank ( 1 yr) , Ashoka Uni Comp Sci [**Varun Menon**](https://www.linkedin.com/in/sureshvarunmenon/)** **- Senior Assc RBI H (3 yrs), Loyola BCom , NLU Masters **TT- Weak Maybe/too early  for Z47 ($1M raise), Maybe for DeVC** Interesting thesis and space in which they are building, however the current product is quite weak (no real workflows like Anuj at OnFi), on sales they are much better on call but no clients yet **Could be interesting to meet and track given reg access and top down sales pull.** + Interesting space - Compliance AI- Hair on Fire problem from an AML and risk perspective + Team - understand how to sell to banks - entrenched with regulators- " Will be one step ahead on regulations - all the folks working on guidelines are mentors" ? No real POCs despite 1 year of being operational ? Very dismissive on competition - " Competition (OnFi) got AMCs cause they''re easy, bank mei aap ko warm intro lena padega to sell" **Selkea** **Product Overview** - Building a compliance ...'),
(431, '**Company Overview**: - Founded October 2023, registered June 2024 - Building automated satellite system for pharmaceutical manufacturing in space - Starting as CRO (Contract Research Organization), evolving to CDMO (Contract Development Manufacturing Organization) - Global focus from day one, despite being an Indian company - Recently raised ₹5 crore from Campus Fund **Mission & Motivation** - Antriksh founded company after his mother''s cancer treatment experience with Keytruda (developed in space) - Identified key pain points in current space pharmaceutical manufacturing: - Limited frequency (can''t do 4 tests/year) - High costs (Merck spent $15M for few ml) - Disruptions from astronauts'' movements affecting gravity - Personal investment: Founder declined Munich job offer, invested full savings **Technology & Innovation** - Three-part satellite system: 1. Satellite bus (purchased off-shelf) 1. Automated pharmaceutical processing module (prototype ready) 1. Re-entry module with proprietary heat shield - Producing pharmaceutical/protein crystals that serve as "blueprint compounds" - Key IP: Lightweight heat shield (1/3 weight of commercial options) - Reusable satellite design enables quarterly missions without building new satellites **Team Structure** - Antriksh - pharmaceutical experiments and payload - Jivitesh - operations and design (previously worked on CAN satellite projects for ISRO) - Monica - space mission planning (former NASA and German Aerospace Center) - Team con...'),
(433, '**Meeting Notes**: **Founder Background- **[**Karan Goyal**](https://www.linkedin.com/in/karan-goyal-6b1099188/) - Origin & early exposure: Grew up in Samana (near Patiala cantonment), surrounded by tanks and artillery; developed early fascination with defense. - Family context: Comes from a business family (yarn mill background), saw entrepreneurship at home. - Education: IIT Delhi graduate, Class of 2022. - Member of the Formula Student race car team for 4 years — hands-on hardware building, teamwork, and exposure to startup culture. - Inspired by seniors who started Baaz Bikes and Vecmocon, both now beyond Series B. - Influences: - Studied US defense-tech ecosystem — particularly Anduril (Palmer Luckey, ex-Oculus, and Palantir alumni). - Read *Kill Chain* by Anduril’s co-founder; internalized concept that modern warfare revolves around building and disrupting the “kill chain.” - Concluded that robotics will disrupt defense the most, creating room for a new “Lockheed Martin.” **Company Formation & Team** - Founded: 2022–23 after noticing drone-based drug smuggling on the India–Pakistan border. - Initial setup: Funded by founder’s father; started in a 2BHK apartment in Gurgaon converted into a workshop. - Co-founders: 5 IIT Delhi graduates. - Initially balanced jobs with building; all now full-time. - Team split: - 2 on business, investment, manufacturing, finance. - 3 on technical verticals: AI on edge (computer vision), radar development, and interceptor engineering. **Tec...')
